# Proposal

## What will (likely) be the title of your project?
Sweet Defense

## In just a sentence or two, summarize your project. (E.g., "A website that lets you buy and sell stocks.")	
A game consisting of towers of pastries that attack incoming customers, satiating their hunger. Defend the towers until the game is over.

## In a paragraph or more, detail your project. What will your software do? What features will it have? How will it be executed?
The software will be an executable file that opens our game. The game will prompt the user to create a character and assign an objective to them. The objective is to defend entities on the plane from other entities that are programmed to destroy or eliminate the initial ones. There will be character interactions, and most actions will be done through a point and click interaction or typing interaction by the user. It will most likely be done through a Game Engine, it will make the coding significantly easier, but it does not change the fact that we will have to learn the library to use it appropriately and efficiently. Thinking about doing it through PyGames or using some other type of Game Engine.

## If planning to collaborate with 1 or 2 classmates for the final project, list their names, email addresses, and the names of their assigned TAs below.
Caohoc Nguyen (tun57054@temple.edu) from Section 007 under TA Sai Shi, Jerry Huang (tun45399@temple.edu) from Section 009 under TA Joanne Nichols.

